## When to use each MCP tool

**get_code_example** — call this BEFORE writing any integration code.
Pass the operation name: "init", "discover", "sale", "refund",
"receipt", "events", "capabilities", "install"
The returned example is the current, compilable, correct pattern.

**explain_error** — call this whenever a PathError is encountered or
when the developer reports an error code.
Returns: meaning, common causes, recoverable flag, suggested fix.
Covers all 13 PathErrorCode values.

**validate_integration** — call this AFTER writing integration code,
before presenting it to the developer for review.
Pass the Swift code snippet as a string.
Returns a list of warnings for common mistakes.

**get_integration_checklist** — call this at the start of any integration
session to show the developer the full journey and what is complete.

**get_info_plist_requirements** — call this when checking or setting up
BLE permissions. Returns ready-to-paste Info.plist XML.

