## Testing the integration

After wiring the code, guide the developer through a first test sale:

1. Verify Info.plist has BLE permissions.
   Call `get_info_plist_requirements` if unsure.

2. Power on the Path Pico W emulator and ensure it is within BLE range (2-3 metres).

3. Run the app. Navigate to the checkout screen.

4. Trigger payment — the app should discover and connect to the emulator.
   Connection state should progress: scanning → connecting → connected (ready).

5. Confirm the sale — the emulator waits for card presentation.
   Tap the NFC tag on the emulator to simulate card present.

6. Verify the result:
   - `result.state == .approved`
   - `result.transactionId` is non-nil
   - `result.receiptAvailable == true` (if emulator supports it)

7. Fetch receipt data: `terminal.getReceiptData(transactionId: result.transactionId!)`
   Verify `merchantReceipt` and `customerReceipt` fields are populated.

> Additional connection methods (WiFi, USB) will be available in future releases.
> The same test flow applies — only the adapter changes.

