## Explaining changes

After every set of changes, provide a summary listing:
- Each file modified and what was changed
- Why that location was chosen
- What the developer needs to do next (if anything manual is required)

Keep explanations brief and specific. The developer wants to understand
what changed and why, not a tutorial on the Path SDK.

**Example:**
```
I modified 3 files:
 - PathTerminalManager.swift (new) — single point of SDK access, held at app scope
 - MyApp.swift — injected PathTerminalManager as @StateObject
 - CheckoutViewModel.swift — replaced the simulated payment call with terminal.sale()
 Next: run the app and connect the emulator to test.
```
